<p>
  ----
</p>
<p>
  It's one thing to know what people are saying - but an entirely different thing to know how people are voting. 
</p>
<p>
  So, I also made nifty toolbar that shows you how your representative voted on bills you care about. 
</p>
<p>
  I didn't want it to be annoying, so it only shows up when you're on a social media or news website - when I care the most.
</p>
<p>
  [[Download Toolbar]]
</p>
<p>
  The toolbar makes it super easy to see how your elected officials are voting on bills related to issues you care about. 
</p>
<p>
  It also lets you call your elected official with a single click. If you like how they voted then you can call and tell them to keep up the good work! Trust me, they love hearing how good of a job they are doing. 
</p>
<p>
  And, if your elected official voted differently than how you want, make sure they know that too!
</p>
<p>
  It’s amazing how much time I spent posting about the news of the day on social media contrasted to how little time I actually spent doing anything. Now I can talk about what I did rather than merely complain and troll random strangers online.
</p>
