</p>
<p>
  ----
</p>
<p>
  The last feature of the toolbar is meant to give you a voice.
</p>
<p>
  Congress has something like a 7% approval rating. Nearly all Americans agree that government is so polarized and partisan that it’s basically worthless. This makes us look stupid in the eyes of the world and Americans are smarter than that. 
</p>
<p>
  We agree on vastly more than we disagree on.
</p>
<p>
  The toolbar lets each person cast a single anonymous and public vote, and make a single statement on any issue they want.
</p>
<p>
  You can change your vote at any time. In fact, we encourage it. Soak in new information. Question assumptions. You should be discussing issues with friends, staying informed, ane evolving your perspectives. 
</p>
<p>
  Votes are recorded on the blockchain. So, you get all the security and privacy features along with the benefit of a decentralized system.
</p>
<p>
  Voter sentiment can be filtered and grouped by congressional district, state, national levels, as well as by political party. The full spectrum of political thought can be put on display through a signle statement that each voter is able to make when casting their vote.
</p>
<p>
  With widespread adoption and sufficient identity management, we could build an authoritative and decentralized voter sentiment model available to the public domain. 
</p>
<p>
  We can show the world that “we the people", on a district by district level, aren't as stupid as our government and political environment currently makes us look. 
</p>
<p>
  We are unified on most issues, and through this technology, we can prove it.
</p>
